fightback tour events at stanford fightback tour facebook twitter email print add to calendar the fightback tour is coming to stanford to commemorate antiwar week of solidarity and in defense of civil liberties marking the ten year anniversary of the war in afghanistan stephen downs ny civil liberties attorney and leading national spokesman against government promoted islamophobia and repression against the muslim american communities and jess sundin chicago grand jury subpoena victim and solidarity antiwar activist facing along with 23 others felony charges of conspiracy to aid and abet terrorism will both be speaking on the repression of civil liberties at home and us wars abroad when wednesday october 19 2011 8 15 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where stanford law school lounge map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags lecture reading public service international sponsor stanford says no to war civil rights and civil liberties society muslim students awareness network stanford american civil liberties union contact jdschott stanford edu admission free and open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 293 29371 last modified october 12 2011
